│                                                                                                                              │
│ My previous patch added a check `if (!T->isFirstClassType()) return false;` at the beginning of the function. The fact that  │
│ execution still reaches the crashing line implies that `T->isFirstClassType()` is returning `true` for the problematic type. │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ Let's re-examine the type from the reproducer: `{ {}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {} }`. This is a struct containing seven empty     │
│ structs. An empty struct `{}` is not a first-class type. A struct containing non-first-class elements is itself not a        │
│ first-class type. Therefore, `isFirstClassType()` should return `false`.                                                     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The only logical explanation for the continued crash is that `isFirstClassType()` is incorrectly returning `true`. This      │
│ suggests a bug in `Type::isFirstClassType()` itself, where it doesn't correctly check the elements of a struct type          │
│ recursively.                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The correct fix is not in the SLP vectorizer, but in the core `Type` implementation in `llvm/lib/IR/Type.cpp`. I need to     │
│ modify `StructType::isFirstClassType()` to iterate over its element types and return `false` if any element is not a         │
│ first-class type.                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will now modify `llvm/lib/IR/Type.cpp` to correctly implement this check.                                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i '/bool StructType::isFirstClassType() const {/a \  for (Type *ElemTy : elements())\n    if                            │
│ (!ElemTy->isFirstClassType())\n      return false;' llvm/lib/IR/Type.cpp                                                     │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
